Mu’azu Sambo, minister of transportation, recently hosted some members of the executive management team of MoFI in Abuja. MoFI is an investment arm of the federal government with about 130 corporate entities. President Muhammadu Buhari had, in January, approved the appointment of the inaugural members of the board and the executive management team of the new Ministry of Finance Incorporated. Armstrong Katang, who is the chief executive officer, led the team. Below are photos. Sambo Adegoroye, minister of state for transport; Magdalene Ajan, permanent secretary (transport); Mu’azu Sambo, minister of transportation, and Armstrong Takang, MD/CEO MOFI.  Sambo with Takang 